HEADWORD: Detour
<hw>De`tour"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧tour</ets>, fr. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧tourner</ets> to turn aside;
pref. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧-</ets> (L. <ets>dis-</ets>) + <ets>tourner</ets> to
turn. See <er>Turn</er>.]</ety> <def>A turning; a circuitous route; a
deviation from a direct course; <as>as, the <ex>detours</ex> of the
Mississippi</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

